payload handler factory:
this return an object
that defines a process_payload()
method, called by uncle archie's
flask server.

uncle archie uses the factory to
create a payload handler object
(from a string provided by the user).

the payload handler receives the
payload and performs a task on it.

payload handlers are high-level objects
that add tasks at an abstract level.



DCPPC Payload Handler:

def process_payload():

    task1 = private_www_build_test()
    task1.run(payload)

    task2 = private_www_integration_test() 
    task2.run(payload)

    # ...


